WEBVTT

00:02.200 --> 00:04.202
OLIVER [VOICE OVER]:
My name is Oliver Queen.

00:04.440 --> 00:11.210
For five years, I was stranded
on an island with only one goal: survive.

00:11.440 --> 00:12.680
Oliver Queen is alive.

00:12.880 --> 00:16.009
OLIVER [VOICE OVER]: Now I will fulfill
my father's dying wish.

00:16.239 --> 00:18.049
To use the list of names he left me...

00:18.280 --> 00:21.090
...and bring down those
who are poisoning my city.

00:21.840 --> 00:24.047
To do this,
I must become someone else.

00:25.840 --> 00:29.287
I must become something else.

00:29.480 --> 00:30.641
NARRATOR:
Previously on Arrow:

00:30.880 --> 00:33.281
DR. LAMB: The Oliver you lost
might not be the one they found.

00:33.480 --> 00:36.609
When you were plotting your plan
to save the city...

00:36.840 --> 00:39.889
...I don't think you considered the effect
it would have on the people in your life.

00:40.080 --> 00:41.127
OLIVER:
You're wrong.

00:41.320 --> 00:45.245
Not being able to tell my family the truth
doesn't hurt anyone worse than me.

00:45.480 --> 00:47.323
I made you a promise I couldn't keep.

00:47.560 --> 00:51.167
After being granted the miracle
of having my child returned to me...

00:51.400 --> 00:54.768
...that you seem to have no interest
in telling me the truth.

00:54.960 --> 00:58.681
You've gotta let me in, Ollie.
You've gotta let someone in.

01:11.160 --> 01:13.162
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:19.920 --> 01:21.126
- Hello?
- Hi.

01:21.320 --> 01:24.324
Mom said I'm supposed to remind you
to pick her up for lunch.

01:24.560 --> 01:26.130
Was I supposed to have lunch with her?

01:26.320 --> 01:28.641
She said she left you five messages.

01:28.840 --> 01:31.366
Bite the bullet
and have a Cobb salad with the woman.

01:31.560 --> 01:34.769
Sometimes it's difficult to remember
which one of you is my mother.

01:35.680 --> 01:40.004
Mrs. Queen, all I'm asking for is a chance
to sit down and discuss our proposal.

01:40.240 --> 01:42.925
If that's all it is,
then I can save us both the time.

01:43.160 --> 01:45.049
-It's rejected.
- I see. May I ask why?

01:45.240 --> 01:47.368
Do I really need to answer that,
Mr. Copani?

01:49.000 --> 01:52.163
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm meeting my son for lunch.

01:55.600 --> 01:57.602
[TIRES SCREECH]

02:05.240 --> 02:06.571
Get down!

02:08.680 --> 02:10.568
[EXHALES]

02:12.680 --> 02:14.569
- Mom? Are you okay?
- I'm all right.

02:14.760 --> 02:15.966
- Are you hurt?
- No, I'm...

02:16.160 --> 02:17.924
- Are you sure?
- I'm fine. I'm fine.

02:18.120 --> 02:20.009
Call 911.

02:29.480 --> 02:31.084
[CAR TIRES SCREECH]

02:49.240 --> 02:52.244
[HORN HONKS]

02:53.560 --> 02:55.961
[PANTING]

03:10.240 --> 03:11.571
Hi.

03:11.760 --> 03:13.967
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

03:14.920 --> 03:17.048
I'm fine.

03:17.800 --> 03:20.770
- Did you reach Walter?
- No, I'm sorry.

03:20.960 --> 03:23.122
As I was telling
your mother and sister...

03:23.320 --> 03:27.086
...the CAT scan showed a grade-2
concussion. She can go home so long...

03:27.280 --> 03:30.090
...as someone stays with her.

03:30.280 --> 03:31.964
- Thank you.
MOIRA: Hm.

03:33.440 --> 03:36.523
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have left you.
I thought you were fine.

03:36.720 --> 03:38.484
What did you think you were doing?

03:38.680 --> 03:41.923
I wanted to get the license plate
of the guy who took a shot at you.

03:42.120 --> 03:45.169
- Well, that was foolish.
- Yeah.

03:53.360 --> 03:56.728
- So did you get the license plate?
- No, he got away.

03:56.960 --> 03:59.930
Maybe you should spend
a little less time trying to be a hero.

04:00.120 --> 04:02.361
You're obviously not very good at it.

04:02.560 --> 04:04.369
- That's cute.
- Wasn't trying to be.

04:04.560 --> 04:09.691
You left Mom in the street.
Alone and hurt in the street.

04:09.880 --> 04:12.724
Heh, to get a license plate?

04:17.760 --> 04:23.767
- You don't believe me?
- I love you. Mom loves you.

04:24.480 --> 04:27.882
But it's getting hard
when you won't be truthful with us.

04:37.120 --> 04:38.360
Detectives.

04:38.560 --> 04:40.927
- Do you have any leads on the shooter?
- Not yet.

04:41.120 --> 04:43.566
- Did you get a look at him?
- He was wearing a helmet.

04:43.800 --> 04:47.088
- Don't worry. We'll find him.
- My head of security is on his way.

04:47.280 --> 04:48.884
I wanna make sure there are men
outside my mother's door.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.570
She needs to be protected.

04:50.760 --> 04:53.843
You know your family's
at the tippy-top of my list of priorities.

04:54.040 --> 04:55.690
The guy she was with was connected.

04:55.880 --> 04:59.965
Mobbed-up-to-the-eyeballs connected.
She wasn't the target.

05:02.920 --> 05:05.287
And you're welcome.

05:08.560 --> 05:10.244
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

05:14.360 --> 05:18.206
Uh, technically, I did get here, like,
1O seconds before this guy.

05:21.080 --> 05:22.127
Keep the change.

05:24.440 --> 05:27.125
So, Tommy,
what brings you by so late?

05:27.320 --> 05:30.642
Well, I assumed, rightly, that you would
be at home working tonight...

05:30.840 --> 05:34.561
...and I also assumed
that you might be hungry. Also rightly.

05:35.320 --> 05:36.401
I don't know.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.405
This is a mushroom and olive pizza
from Mario's.

05:39.600 --> 05:41.762
Oh, that is damn good pie.

05:43.200 --> 05:47.569
- All right. What do you have to offer?
- Spicy tuna on crispy rice from Toro.

05:47.760 --> 05:49.205
Oh.

05:49.400 --> 05:52.927
Damn you, Merlyn.
I hope sushi was all you had in mind.

05:53.160 --> 05:57.006
Uh, actually, there was something
that I wanted to ask you.

05:57.200 --> 06:00.409
- And what's that?
- Will you go out with me?

06:00.600 --> 06:02.648
Like, on a date?

06:02.880 --> 06:05.121
You brought me dinner
to ask me to dinner?

06:05.320 --> 06:08.403
Oh, uh, well, I also did throw you
a really big charity gala.

06:08.600 --> 06:12.161
See, I thought you threw it for
the hundreds of people it would benefit.

06:12.360 --> 06:15.807
Oh, yeah, hundreds of people.
Plus one more.

06:16.000 --> 06:17.570
- Tommy, heh.
- Laurel.

06:17.760 --> 06:20.809
I get it. Okay, this is all happening
for us in the wrong order.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.401
First, we're friends for many years...

06:23.600 --> 06:26.888
...and then, briefly,
we are friends with benefits...

06:27.080 --> 06:31.085
...extremely excellent benefits,
and now I'm just hoping...

06:31.320 --> 06:34.290
...that we can be two people
sitting at the same restaurant...

06:34.480 --> 06:36.767
...at the same table at the same time.

06:36.960 --> 06:40.442
See, when I say it like that,
it doesn't sound so scary, does it?

06:47.360 --> 06:49.124
Oliver, your mom's nearly killed...

06:49.320 --> 06:52.005
...I think you can take a day off
from training.

06:52.200 --> 06:54.680
My mother wasn't the target.

06:54.880 --> 06:56.086
This man was. Paul Copani.

06:56.280 --> 06:58.123
He was trying to close a deal with her
when they were shot at.

06:58.320 --> 06:59.481
[PANTING]

06:59.680 --> 07:01.648
Copani works
for Bertinelli Construction.

07:01.840 --> 07:04.810
- And Frank Bertinelli.
- The mob boss.

07:05.000 --> 07:06.490
I did some digging.

07:06.680 --> 07:09.809
Copani isn't the first member
of Bertinelli's crew who's been hit.

07:10.000 --> 07:11.047
You did some digging.

07:11.280 --> 07:13.328
Bertinelli has a lot of enemies.

07:13.520 --> 07:16.808
The best way to figure out
who's trying to target his organization...

07:17.000 --> 07:20.288
-...is to get inside of it.
- So let me get this right, Oliver.

07:20.480 --> 07:24.371
Your mother's shot at, nearly killed, and
the way you process this emotionally...

07:24.560 --> 07:28.884
-...is by going undercover with the mob.
- I'm not trying to process it emotionally.

07:29.080 --> 07:31.890
Yeah, well,
maybe that's your problem, man.

07:32.080 --> 07:35.687
You ever thought about
just being there for your family?

07:36.720 --> 07:38.688
I tried that today with Thea.

07:38.880 --> 07:41.724
She told me I wasn't being honest
with her and she's right.

07:42.480 --> 07:45.529
I can't very well explain to her
that I left our mother alone...

07:45.720 --> 07:48.690
...and bleeding on the pavement
because I'm fast enough...

07:48.880 --> 07:51.167
...to almost run down the attacker.

07:53.760 --> 07:57.526
But what I can do
is protect my family.

07:58.960 --> 08:05.809
And, Diggle, when I find out
who this guy is, he's a dead man.

08:48.480 --> 08:51.404
- Speedy, where you going?
- Clubbing.

08:51.600 --> 08:54.729
Which is difficult to do in your house
and not at an actual club.

08:54.920 --> 08:56.809
I have to go out tonight.

08:57.400 --> 09:00.802
- I thought you'd be watching Mom.
- I've spent the whole day with her.

09:01.000 --> 09:04.925
- I thought you were taking the night shift.
- I'm sorry, but this thing, it's important.

09:05.120 --> 09:06.167
[SIGHS]

09:06.360 --> 09:09.523
You know, sometimes, Ollie,
I just don't get you.

09:09.720 --> 09:11.768
And by "sometimes" I mean never.

09:11.960 --> 09:14.486
You're not the first person
to say that to me today.

09:14.680 --> 09:16.330
Why am I not surprised?

09:17.720 --> 09:21.645
- Oh, nice dress. Where you headed?
- Upstairs. Apparently.

09:22.680 --> 09:25.206
- Long story.
- Hey, I heard about your mom.

09:25.400 --> 09:27.687
- Is she all right?
- Well, she's resting upstairs.

09:27.920 --> 09:29.331
More shaken up than anything.

09:29.520 --> 09:32.603
I gotta run to this, uh, business thing.
I appreciate you stopping by.

09:32.840 --> 09:35.286
No problem.
Just so long as your mom's all right.

09:35.480 --> 09:37.084
Yeah.

09:37.280 --> 09:39.681
Hey, one more thing.

09:40.720 --> 09:44.122
Mainly because I don't want you
to find this out from someone else...

09:44.320 --> 09:46.971
...that someone else
especially being Laurel...

09:47.160 --> 09:48.525
...uh...

09:48.720 --> 09:52.691
...we're going to dinner,
as in a, uh, date.

09:54.080 --> 09:55.286
That's good.

09:55.480 --> 09:58.609
Laurel deserves someone special
and so do you.

09:59.040 --> 10:00.087
Thanks, man.

10:00.320 --> 10:02.800
- I gotta run to this thing.
- Absolutely. I'll catch you later.

10:03.000 --> 10:06.686
Oh, and, uh, Tommy, if you hurt her,
I'll snap your neck.

10:07.960 --> 10:09.610
I'm just kidding, heh.

10:15.600 --> 10:17.125
[DOORBELL RINGS]

10:20.680 --> 10:21.727
Mr. Bertinelli.

10:22.920 --> 10:24.888
- Call me Frank.
- Call me Oliver.

10:25.080 --> 10:26.730
Yeah, heh.

10:27.160 --> 10:29.527
Thank you for agreeing to meet me
at my home.

10:29.720 --> 10:32.485
Living rooms make
the best conference rooms.

10:32.680 --> 10:34.523
- Oh, I'm gonna steal that.
- Heh.

10:34.720 --> 10:38.247
- Nick Salvati, my associate.
- How do you do?

10:38.440 --> 10:40.363
Let's have a drink.

10:50.720 --> 10:52.449
THEA:
So, what are you in the mood for, hmm?

10:52.640 --> 10:58.647
We could watch reality housewife
cooking show or Cop Docs.

10:58.880 --> 11:01.281
It's where doctors run around
fighting crime...

11:01.480 --> 11:03.130
...when they're not all
sleeping with each other.

11:03.320 --> 11:04.401
[CHUCKLES]

11:04.640 --> 11:06.210
Whatever you want, sweetheart.

11:06.400 --> 11:08.368
You're the one who's given up
your evening out.

11:08.600 --> 11:11.683
Aw, it's not like there's anybody else
who could be staying with you.

11:11.880 --> 11:12.927
[GASPS]

11:13.120 --> 11:16.408
- Oh, wait, yes, there is.
- Don't be too harsh on your brother.

11:16.600 --> 11:17.931
[SCOFFS]

11:18.120 --> 11:21.920
Why not? I mean,
aren't you getting, heh, sick of his lies?

11:24.200 --> 11:26.806
Thea, everyone has secrets.

11:27.600 --> 11:31.525
I mean, we all have things
that we wanna keep to ourselves.

11:34.120 --> 11:35.963
I just don't get him sometimes.

11:38.120 --> 11:39.690
I know.

11:41.200 --> 11:43.009
I know.

11:46.920 --> 11:50.322
You know, being in that hospital
and seeing Dr. Lamb again...

11:50.560 --> 11:54.121
...it made me remember the day
that Oliver came home.

11:56.640 --> 11:59.530
It was Dr. Lamb that told me
that the Oliver we'd lost...

11:59.720 --> 12:02.121
...might not be the Oliver
that they'd found.

12:02.360 --> 12:08.686
I think it's easy to forget, but he lived
apart from civilization for 5 years.

12:08.880 --> 12:09.927
THEA:
Hm.

12:10.160 --> 12:16.122
- So, what, he gets, like, a free pass?
- No, no, no, not at all.

12:17.000 --> 12:20.766
I just think we need to stop judging him
for the Oliver he was...

12:20.960 --> 12:25.170
...and start accepting him
for the Oliver that he is.

12:26.960 --> 12:32.330
So, Oliver, I'll be honest with you,
I was surprised to hear from you.

12:32.560 --> 12:34.210
It was my impression from the news...

12:34.440 --> 12:37.011
...that you weren't gonna be involved
with your family's business.

12:37.200 --> 12:40.363
There were a few catchphrases I missed
while I was away for five years.

12:40.560 --> 12:42.210
One of them being
lame-stream media.

12:42.440 --> 12:43.771
[ALL CHUCKLE]

12:43.960 --> 12:46.964
- The press never gets anything right.
- Oh, I know a thing or two about that.

12:47.200 --> 12:48.565
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

12:48.760 --> 12:50.808
- So, Oliver, I'll be blunt.
- Hmm?

12:51.040 --> 12:52.121
I want the contract...

12:52.320 --> 12:55.085
...to build Queen Consolidated's
new applied sciences division.

12:55.280 --> 12:59.171
- And I'm inclined to give it to you.
- Your mother wasn't so enthusiastic.

12:59.920 --> 13:03.845
- How is she by the way?
- She's recuperating at home, thank you.

13:04.040 --> 13:05.280
What a terrible thing.

13:05.480 --> 13:09.963
And, Frank, I was very sorry to hear
about what happened to Paul Copani.

13:10.160 --> 13:14.290
Paul was a good friend.
He was a good man.

13:14.520 --> 13:15.726
[SIGHS]

13:15.920 --> 13:17.365
The violence in this city...

13:17.600 --> 13:19.125
Sometimes I wonder why I stay.

13:19.360 --> 13:21.727
I had the same thought.

13:22.400 --> 13:24.402
So Why'd you come back?

13:24.600 --> 13:27.080
You could have settled
anywhere in the world.

13:27.320 --> 13:29.004
Because Starling City is my home.

13:30.040 --> 13:32.088
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

13:34.760 --> 13:38.287
No matter which way you go or turn,
you always end up at home.

13:39.440 --> 13:43.286
- Oliver, this is my daughter, Helena.
- Hello.

13:43.960 --> 13:48.887
- Nice to meet you. I'm heading out.
- All right. Take one of the guys with you.

13:49.080 --> 13:51.082
- I can take care of myself.
- Heh.

13:52.640 --> 13:54.369
I wasn't asking, sweetie.

13:54.600 --> 13:58.889
Frank, that meeting you requested?
They can do it.

13:59.560 --> 14:00.607
Now.

14:03.400 --> 14:07.803
- I can come back another time.
- No, no, no. Just, uh...

14:09.520 --> 14:11.363
Just excuse us for a moment,
would you?

14:11.560 --> 14:13.483
OLIVER: Mm-hm.
- Thank you.

14:16.120 --> 14:20.284
Oliver Queen.
The rich man's Lindsay Lohan.

14:21.160 --> 14:22.764
Look, um...

14:24.280 --> 14:26.203
...I've gotta go to this other meeting.

14:26.400 --> 14:28.323
But I need someone
to take him to dinner.

14:28.520 --> 14:29.965
So you pimp out your daughter.

14:30.160 --> 14:32.925
No, I ask her to help me
close a business deal.

14:33.120 --> 14:36.169
I remind her
that the family business is dying...

14:36.360 --> 14:39.682
...and that we need this contract
and Oliver Queen can give it to us.

14:39.880 --> 14:43.965
Please, sweet pea, huh?
For us. For me, hmm?

14:45.240 --> 14:46.924
That's my girl.

14:47.120 --> 14:50.647
Oliver, I'm so sorry,
something has come up.

14:50.840 --> 14:54.322
But Helena would love to take you
to dinner and discuss the deal further.

14:54.520 --> 14:55.726
- Oh.
HELENA: Hm.

14:55.920 --> 14:57.410
I was hoping to speak with you.

14:57.600 --> 15:02.288
Well, as you, uh, speak for your family,
my daughter also speaks for ours.

15:03.000 --> 15:06.288
It's really not necessary.

15:08.240 --> 15:10.641
-It'd be my pleasure.
- Sure.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.082
I look forward to working together.

15:34.600 --> 15:38.161
FRANK: Thank you for coming.
- Anything for a friend.

15:38.360 --> 15:41.170
[SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

15:44.520 --> 15:47.285
We're not responsible
for the attacks on your people.

15:47.480 --> 15:54.329
These attacks on my business,
on my family's lifeblood, they stop now.

15:54.520 --> 15:55.681
Or I'm coming for you.

16:02.680 --> 16:03.761
[SIGHS]

16:03.960 --> 16:07.169
What does the Triad have to gain
by provoking you?

16:07.400 --> 16:11.724
Well, no one ever credited the Triad
with rational thinking.

16:13.720 --> 16:15.848
If not them, then who?

16:16.040 --> 16:17.371
FRANK [OVER COMPUTER]:
Whoever it is...

16:17.560 --> 16:19.801
...when I find out who's behind this,
there will be blood.

16:20.040 --> 16:22.407
Bertinelli's ready to put the screws
to everyone...

16:22.600 --> 16:24.204
...who pays him protection money.

16:24.400 --> 16:26.721
Three of his best earners
have been murdered.

16:26.960 --> 16:28.769
He's gotta make up the cash
somewhere.

16:29.000 --> 16:33.562
Whoever is pruning the family tree
is looking to make Bertinelli suffer.

16:33.800 --> 16:36.326
- You think it's one of the other families?
- No.

16:36.520 --> 16:37.681
HILTON:
Then who?

16:37.880 --> 16:40.770
According to the coroner,
none of the vics took a clean shot.

16:40.960 --> 16:43.645
Half the bullets missed.
Our killer is not a pro.

16:43.840 --> 16:46.241
That's not stopping them
from pulling that trigger.

16:46.480 --> 16:47.925
That's up to us.

16:49.480 --> 16:51.960
Or this is gonna blow up
into an all-out mob war.

17:01.200 --> 17:05.523
- You're an angel, Helena. So beautiful.
- Heh.

17:06.160 --> 17:09.561
Well, we are gonna take good care
of both of you tonight.

17:09.760 --> 17:14.321
- You'll tell your father hello from us?
- Of course, Mr. Russo.

17:14.520 --> 17:16.284
- I'll give you a minute.
- Thank you.

17:19.760 --> 17:21.808
I heard about your mother's accident.

17:22.000 --> 17:25.209
- Is she gonna be okay?
- She's gonna be fine. Thanks.

17:26.319 --> 17:28.084
I'm glad.

17:30.760 --> 17:35.402
So why would you wanna go
into business with my father?

17:35.600 --> 17:38.410
You know who he is
and how he made his money.

17:38.600 --> 17:40.807
You don't approve
of your family's enterprises?

17:41.000 --> 17:42.206
We share a name.

17:42.400 --> 17:45.483
That name defines us
whether we want it to or not.

17:45.680 --> 17:47.762
You've already made judgments
about me...

17:48.000 --> 17:49.889
...like I've made judgments about you.

17:50.080 --> 17:52.811
Right.
I'm the rich man's Lindsay Lohan.

17:53.320 --> 17:55.527
Heh, sorry.

17:56.360 --> 17:58.169
- That's okay.
- Heh.

18:01.240 --> 18:04.449
- Hey, can I ask you something?
- Yeah.

18:04.680 --> 18:07.286
I know it must have been hell for you...

18:07.520 --> 18:10.763
...alone on that island for five years,
but, um...

18:12.520 --> 18:13.646
But what?

18:15.120 --> 18:20.809
But was there ever a day when you were
just happy to be away from everything?

18:21.480 --> 18:22.845
No pressure from your family.

18:23.080 --> 18:26.402
No need to be the person
that everyone else expects you to be.

18:26.600 --> 18:31.083
- Was there ever a day when--?
- When I didn't feel lost, that I felt...

18:31.280 --> 18:32.406
...free?

18:34.680 --> 18:35.727
[CHUCKLES]

18:35.960 --> 18:38.850
More than one and, uh...

18:40.480 --> 18:42.847
And those are the days that I miss.

18:47.880 --> 18:50.690
[TOMMY GASPS THEN COUGHS]

18:50.880 --> 18:54.168
- What, is it too spicy for you, Merlyn?
- No. No, not really.

18:54.400 --> 18:58.530
I'm just, um, crying because I was thinking
of a Hallmark commercial...

18:58.720 --> 19:01.530
...I saw earlier today
featuring a sick kitty.

19:02.080 --> 19:03.491
It was very emotional.

19:03.680 --> 19:05.205
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

19:05.400 --> 19:08.609
WAITER: Will there be anything else?
- No, thank you.

19:08.800 --> 19:10.370
Yep.

19:11.520 --> 19:13.761
Thanks for letting me
take you to dinner.

19:14.360 --> 19:16.647
Well, thank you
for letting me choose Indian.

19:18.120 --> 19:22.887
Yeah, I read this article
by a film critic once who said...

19:23.080 --> 19:27.608
...if he could have one wish it would be
to watch his favorite movie again...

19:27.800 --> 19:29.290
...for the first time.

19:30.280 --> 19:32.601
I kind of wish that was us.

19:33.160 --> 19:35.401
So you want dinner and a movie?

19:35.920 --> 19:37.604
No.

19:38.280 --> 19:42.604
I wish we had just met,
and that all this was just beginning...

19:42.800 --> 19:47.442
...and there wasn't so much of me
I wish you'd forget.

19:47.640 --> 19:49.802
Well, keep saying nice things
like that...

19:50.040 --> 19:52.805
...and maybe next time
I'll let you choose the restaurant.

19:56.240 --> 19:57.287
- Mr. Merlyn?
- Yeah.

19:57.480 --> 20:00.165
I'm sorry, I'm afraid your credit card
has been declined.

20:00.360 --> 20:03.489
You swipe it a few times?
Sometimes those things can be glitchy.

20:03.720 --> 20:08.647
I did. And, um, I'm afraid the credit card
company wants me to confiscate it.

20:10.240 --> 20:11.924
Sorry.

20:13.840 --> 20:17.401
OLIVER: People are always asking me
what did I miss the most.

20:17.600 --> 20:19.329
[SIGHS]

20:19.520 --> 20:24.481
Uh, air conditioning.
Satellite radio. Taglia...

20:24.680 --> 20:25.920
- Tagliatelle?
- Right.

20:26.160 --> 20:27.207
Hmm.

20:27.400 --> 20:31.166
Those are the answers I give because
those are the answers they're expecting.

20:31.360 --> 20:35.126
- Why can't you just be truthful?
- I don't know how truthful I can be.

20:36.200 --> 20:40.410
You've been through a crucible.
And it changed you. How could it not?

20:43.280 --> 20:45.681
That's beautiful. Your cross.

20:48.160 --> 20:52.927
-It's a gift. From my fiancé.
- Heh, fiancé.

20:53.120 --> 20:58.001
- I didn't know you were engaged.
- I'm not. Anymore.

20:59.120 --> 21:01.566
- He died.
- I'm sorry.

21:02.400 --> 21:04.129
Me too.

21:04.640 --> 21:07.211
That was my crucible.

21:09.840 --> 21:12.161
Boy, it's nice to...

21:13.000 --> 21:16.004
It's really nice to be with someone
that I can be myself with.

21:16.520 --> 21:18.921
It's nice to be with someone
who knows how hard it can be.

21:19.120 --> 21:20.167
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

21:20.360 --> 21:22.681
- Ugh, I'm really sorry.
-It's okay. Take it.

21:22.920 --> 21:24.445
Thank you.

21:25.040 --> 21:26.690
- Yeah.
DIGGLE: Hey, it's Dig.

21:26.880 --> 21:27.927
Something came up.

21:28.120 --> 21:30.600
You gotta get out of there
and call me back.

21:31.800 --> 21:35.327
Helena, I have to go.
There's something that I have to do.

21:35.560 --> 21:39.724
It's about my mother.
Otherwise, I would, uh, stay.

21:39.920 --> 21:41.206
And I would like that.

21:43.880 --> 21:48.329
Uh, my father would kill me
if I let you pay.

21:52.320 --> 21:53.731
[SCOFFS]

21:55.400 --> 21:57.209
I have a confession.

21:59.320 --> 22:02.449
- I didn't wanna go out with you tonight.
- That makes two of us.

22:02.640 --> 22:04.005
I'm really glad that I did.

22:04.560 --> 22:05.800
That makes two of us.

22:06.000 --> 22:07.490
[CHUCKLES]

22:07.720 --> 22:09.722
Oliver.

22:10.320 --> 22:12.163
Be careful with my father.

22:19.720 --> 22:20.767
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

22:20.960 --> 22:22.610
Thea, you don't need to knock,
sweetheart.

22:22.800 --> 22:23.847
[DOOR OPENS]

22:24.040 --> 22:25.610
MAN:
What about me?

22:26.080 --> 22:27.127
I hope you don't mind.

22:28.400 --> 22:30.004
Thea let me in.

22:30.240 --> 22:31.366
What are you doing here?

22:31.560 --> 22:33.403
I wanted to see how your recovery
was going.

22:33.600 --> 22:35.728
Surely someone of your means
has a telephone.

22:35.920 --> 22:39.367
I like to see someone when I have
something important to talk about.

22:42.160 --> 22:43.605
We used to be friends, Moira.

22:45.880 --> 22:48.087
I still remember that time.

22:48.280 --> 22:50.726
You, me and Robert.

22:51.560 --> 22:54.006
Which is why I came by.

22:55.160 --> 22:58.960
You are a vital part
of Starling City's future.

22:59.680 --> 23:02.047
Robert feared that future.

23:02.760 --> 23:05.081
He lost his conviction.

23:06.360 --> 23:10.081
It's been my experience that
when someone has a brush with death...

23:10.320 --> 23:16.726
...like you experienced today, even their
deepest held convictions can change.

23:17.720 --> 23:21.361
- Have they?
- No.

23:22.480 --> 23:24.084
You didn't have to say it.

23:27.240 --> 23:29.049
I can see that they haven't.

23:35.720 --> 23:38.200
- What happened?
- Yeah, it's what's about to happen.

23:38.400 --> 23:40.129
Bertinelli's enforcer, Nick Salvati?

23:40.320 --> 23:43.847
Yeah, we drank a Scotch together,
he seems like a real stand-up mobster.

23:44.040 --> 23:47.123
He's paying visits to everyone
who owes the mob protection money.

23:47.360 --> 23:49.966
I'm trying to figure out
who took a shot at my mother...

23:50.160 --> 23:51.969
...not take on all of organized crime.

23:52.200 --> 23:55.044
Salvati and his goons have put
four people in the hospital...

23:55.280 --> 23:57.123
...and if somebody doesn't stop him...

23:57.320 --> 23:59.641
...the poor bastard
who owns Russo's is next.

23:59.840 --> 24:02.525
- Wait, wait. Russo's?
-It's at the corner of Adams--

24:02.720 --> 24:04.563
I know where it is. I'm here right now.

24:04.760 --> 24:06.285
What?

24:06.480 --> 24:08.687
I was having dinner
with Bertinelli's daughter.

24:08.920 --> 24:10.524
You're supposed to be undercover...

24:10.760 --> 24:12.888
-...not speed dating.
- I didn't have a choice.

24:13.080 --> 24:18.041
Yeah, well, uh, I've seen her on the web.
You made quite the sacrifice.

24:22.280 --> 24:24.886
Salvati's here.

24:30.560 --> 24:32.528
I'm sorry, we're closed.

24:35.200 --> 24:38.568
Huh? Mr. Salvati.

24:39.680 --> 24:41.205
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

24:42.120 --> 24:46.330
- Uh, I have some fresh-made lasagna.
SALVATI: We're not here for food, Mr. Russo.

24:47.160 --> 24:50.562
- Your payment's due.
- I already made my payment this month.

24:50.800 --> 24:52.802
You need to pay again.

24:53.000 --> 24:55.207
I can't afford to make
another payment if I'm--

24:55.400 --> 24:59.007
Going to what? Restock your bar?

25:01.680 --> 25:04.365
- Break his fingers.
- Leave him alone!

25:04.600 --> 25:06.284
- Break hers too.
- No, don't touch her!

25:06.520 --> 25:08.602
[EXPLODES]

25:09.520 --> 25:10.567
[MAN GRUNTS]

25:10.760 --> 25:12.000
OLIVER:
Go!

25:12.360 --> 25:13.407
[GUNSHOTS]

25:23.760 --> 25:26.764
[BOTH GRUNTING]

25:32.640 --> 25:34.051
[PANTING]

25:46.680 --> 25:48.091
OLIVER:
I don't understand.

25:48.280 --> 25:50.647
- Why is she targeting her family?
- I don't know.

25:50.840 --> 25:54.162
- Here I thought you had parental issues.
- This is not a joke, Diggle.

25:54.400 --> 25:56.721
Oliver, you're not falling for this girl,
are you?

25:56.920 --> 25:59.446
Because I know
you can't be that crazy.

25:59.640 --> 26:01.449
Helena Bertinelli shot at your mother.

26:01.640 --> 26:03.847
She also murdered four men
in cold blood.

26:04.080 --> 26:08.051
She has to have reasons
for what she's doing.

26:08.840 --> 26:10.683
Reasons?

26:11.400 --> 26:13.846
Since when do you care
about the bad guy's reasons?

26:14.040 --> 26:17.408
Oh, she is bad guy, Oliver.
She's the killer.

26:17.600 --> 26:20.001
Whatever's going on in your head,
get it straight.

26:20.200 --> 26:22.601
Any attempt on his right hand...

26:22.800 --> 26:26.282
...is gonna send your new friend's father
on a Warpath.

26:29.560 --> 26:30.686
I know what I'm doing.

26:35.080 --> 26:37.686
Now I know how your family feels
when you lie to them.

26:43.800 --> 26:45.450
Is this the only angle you've got?

26:45.640 --> 26:48.325
The Russos chintzed out a bit
on their security package.

26:48.520 --> 26:51.285
Somebody's in the wings with a gun
shooting at these guys.

26:51.480 --> 26:54.450
- What do you got from earlier? Yeah.
- Before the shooting?

26:54.640 --> 26:57.325
Business dinner, birthday dinner,
couple of blind dates.

26:57.520 --> 26:59.568
Any guests
of the Chinese persuasion?

26:59.800 --> 27:01.211
- Why?
- Humor me.

27:06.720 --> 27:07.926
Whoa, whoa.

27:08.120 --> 27:11.169
- Wait. Wait a second, what was that?
- Help yourself.

27:11.680 --> 27:12.966
Come on.

27:18.440 --> 27:20.488
Son of a bitch.

27:22.560 --> 27:23.721
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

27:27.760 --> 27:30.161
Detective. ls everything okay?

27:32.400 --> 27:34.129
Your, um...

27:34.320 --> 27:36.846
Your buddy with the arrows
was at Russo's last night.

27:37.040 --> 27:43.400
And I was there earlier with a date. So,
what, you think I'm the hood guy again?

27:44.120 --> 27:46.407
Heh,no.

27:47.080 --> 27:51.768
Your date. Helena Bertinelli.
If I were you, I'd stay away from her.

27:51.960 --> 27:54.042
Her family is bad news on a good day.

27:55.280 --> 27:57.567
Why the sudden concern
for my well-being?

28:00.920 --> 28:03.491
A few weeks ago, I made a mistake.

28:04.280 --> 28:05.770
I almost got you killed.

28:07.880 --> 28:09.564
And you felt like you owed me one?

28:10.360 --> 28:14.285
If I did, as far as I'm concerned,
this clears the books.

28:26.640 --> 28:29.803
Can I talk to you? Dad.

28:30.000 --> 28:33.607
MALCOLM: In case you haven't noticed,
I'm a little occupied at the moment.

28:33.800 --> 28:36.883
I just talked to the accountant.
He said my accounts were frozen.

28:37.080 --> 28:39.321
He said my credit cards
were all canceled.

28:39.520 --> 28:42.922
MALCOLM: I pay Sandy a king's ransom
each year in fees, Tommy.

28:43.760 --> 28:47.731
When it comes to money,
if he says it's so, it's so.

28:47.920 --> 28:50.241
Do you think this is a joke?

28:51.720 --> 28:53.006
MALCOLM:
No.

28:53.200 --> 28:54.247
[PANTING]

28:54.440 --> 28:56.249
You are.

28:57.600 --> 29:00.365
Although, I must say,
your chronic irresponsibility...

29:00.560 --> 29:04.121
...and terminal laziness
has lost its humor.

29:05.480 --> 29:06.527
Heh.

29:06.760 --> 29:08.250
You're wondering why now.

29:08.440 --> 29:13.082
- The better question is why not sooner?
-It's...

29:13.280 --> 29:18.650
-it's my trust fund.
- Which is comprised of my money.

29:18.840 --> 29:21.161
Oh, excuse me.

29:23.480 --> 29:26.086
Was comprised.

30:03.080 --> 30:04.127
Helena.

30:05.640 --> 30:10.202
- How did you find me here?
- I followed you from your house.

30:11.440 --> 30:12.646
Your fiancé?

30:15.920 --> 30:17.490
Yeah.

30:23.200 --> 30:26.409
You said that losing him
was your crucible.

30:26.880 --> 30:30.362
That it changed you.
You didn't say how.

30:35.000 --> 30:38.721
When you love someone
as much as I loved him...

30:38.920 --> 30:40.604
...with all of your heart...

30:40.800 --> 30:45.522
...then you can't just turn that emotion
off when they're taken from you.

30:46.040 --> 30:49.567
You still feel things as deeply.
And if it...

30:49.760 --> 30:52.525
If it can't be love that you feel...

30:54.600 --> 30:55.965
...then it becomes hate.

30:56.720 --> 30:58.131
Hate for who?

30:59.160 --> 31:00.924
Oliver.

31:06.360 --> 31:08.203
You should stay away from me.

31:11.000 --> 31:12.047
Helena.

31:19.400 --> 31:21.050
Get in.

31:30.760 --> 31:33.730
My father is going to kill you for this.

31:33.920 --> 31:35.160
[CHUCKLES]

31:35.640 --> 31:37.404
[GRUNTS]

31:41.480 --> 31:46.327
I've been wanting to do that for years,
you spoiled bitch.

31:47.120 --> 31:51.842
I knew it was someone from the inside
waging war against your father and me.

31:52.040 --> 31:54.850
I just never thought it'd be this inside.

31:55.400 --> 31:57.050
[SCOFFS]

31:59.400 --> 32:01.801
You dropped this at Russo's.

32:02.640 --> 32:04.961
You're smarter
than I gave you credit for, Nicky.

32:05.640 --> 32:08.041
- You're not.
- Hey!

32:10.280 --> 32:13.363
You're a businessman, right?
So let's talk business.

32:13.560 --> 32:15.881
I can offer you a lot of money
if you let us go.

32:16.120 --> 32:20.364
This isn't about money, Richie Rich.
This is about loyalty.

32:20.880 --> 32:22.803
HELENA: He's got nothing to do
with any of this.

32:23.040 --> 32:28.285
SALVATI: Then what the hell is it about?
- My father had Michael murdered.

32:28.480 --> 32:30.403
[SALVATI CHUCKLES]

32:31.760 --> 32:35.651
Of course he did.
He didn't want you to know the truth.

32:35.840 --> 32:39.811
Your rat of a fiance
was gathering evidence.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.571
He was talking to the frigging FBI.

32:42.760 --> 32:46.287
The love of your life
was going to destroy your father.

32:46.520 --> 32:47.681
You're wrong.

32:47.880 --> 32:49.370
[GRUNTS]

32:50.200 --> 32:52.885
We found a laptop in Michael's bag,
Helena.

32:53.080 --> 32:56.448
Everything that could send your father
and me to prison...

32:56.640 --> 32:58.608
...for the rest of our lives was on it.

32:58.800 --> 33:01.406
- That computer--
- Was mine.

33:02.880 --> 33:07.329
Michael wasn't the one
talking to the FBI. I was.

33:08.560 --> 33:12.087
- You?
- My father is a monster...

33:12.280 --> 33:15.329
...who doesn't care who he hurts
to keep his money and power.

33:15.520 --> 33:17.124
And I wanted it to stop.

33:17.320 --> 33:19.800
SALVATI: Well, then it's your fault
Michael's dead.

33:20.000 --> 33:23.925
Not your father for ordering the hit
or me for carrying it out.

33:26.560 --> 33:27.686
Yours.

33:28.560 --> 33:31.370
You shot Michael?

33:34.360 --> 33:37.728
In the chest. So he knew it was me.

33:39.000 --> 33:43.244
Just like this.

33:46.440 --> 33:48.442
[ALL GRUNTING AND GROANING]

34:14.719 --> 34:16.404
You're gonna burn in hell.

34:16.600 --> 34:18.601
It'll be worth it.

34:23.159 --> 34:24.206
[PANTING]

34:24.400 --> 34:25.447
Helena?

34:27.080 --> 34:28.570
[PANTING]

34:29.280 --> 34:31.168
I didn't have a choice, Oliver.

34:32.520 --> 34:34.887
No one can know my secret.

34:41.239 --> 34:44.289
CSU didn't find any usable prints
except for the three victims'.

34:44.480 --> 34:46.208
One of them had a GSW to the chest.

34:46.400 --> 34:49.722
So who broke the necks
of Salvati and his buddy?

34:49.920 --> 34:53.208
Look, it's been a while
since the hood broke anyone's neck.

34:53.440 --> 34:55.408
And I didn't see any arrows
laying around.

34:55.600 --> 34:59.082
Well, better pray that Frank Bertinelli
blames the hood for this.

34:59.320 --> 35:01.482
Because if he thinks it's the Triad...

35:01.680 --> 35:04.126
...Starling City is ground zero
to World War Ill.

35:04.320 --> 35:05.924
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:11.800 --> 35:13.290
You Okay?

35:14.440 --> 35:18.445
- Spoke to my dad today.
- I bet that was fun.

35:18.640 --> 35:21.962
He explained to me what happened
with my credit card yesterday.

35:22.160 --> 35:24.481
And my checking account,
my savings account...

35:24.720 --> 35:28.725
...my brokerage account,
my stock portfolio.

35:29.680 --> 35:33.207
He cut me off completely.

35:34.840 --> 35:36.410
What?

35:36.880 --> 35:38.928
My car got repossessed. That was fun.

35:39.120 --> 35:42.727
And I have to move out of my apartment
by the end of the month.

35:45.960 --> 35:48.486
You are gonna be fine, Tommy.

35:48.680 --> 35:49.727
[SCOFFS]

35:49.920 --> 35:52.446
In fact, you are gonna be great.

35:53.720 --> 35:56.007
Merlyn money or not.

35:58.720 --> 36:00.882
And, you know...

36:02.400 --> 36:05.882
...I have a mushroom
and olive Mario pizza...

36:06.080 --> 36:09.243
...in my refrigerator
waiting to be eaten.

36:10.680 --> 36:14.890
- I suppose it's already paid for, right?
- Exactly.

36:31.600 --> 36:34.080
- When did you get back?
- Just now.

36:34.280 --> 36:35.770
[SIGHS]

36:42.120 --> 36:45.522
- I'm so happy to see you.
- Hmm.

36:46.560 --> 36:49.643
But did you come home only
because you heard I was hurt?

36:50.280 --> 36:51.805
No.

36:52.000 --> 36:53.968
I was already on my way
when Thea called.

36:54.640 --> 36:59.043
I actually came home
because I missed my wife.

37:06.400 --> 37:07.526
MOIRA:
It's okay.

37:09.640 --> 37:12.166
- Is she all right?
- Walter's home.

37:13.120 --> 37:14.531
She's gonna be fine.

37:14.720 --> 37:18.327
Look, I'm sorry if I was a bitch
with you earlier.

37:19.240 --> 37:20.321
There were a few times.

37:20.520 --> 37:22.568
- Could you be more specific?
- Don't push it.

37:22.800 --> 37:25.531
Don't worry. You weren't a bitch.

37:26.040 --> 37:28.407
At the hospital, you were a little...
A little bit.

37:28.640 --> 37:29.766
[CHUCKLES]

37:29.960 --> 37:33.760
Look, I'm just worried about you.

37:34.600 --> 37:39.242
You seem really lonely.
And we all have our secrets, Ollie.

37:39.480 --> 37:42.086
Clearly you have yours.

37:42.840 --> 37:46.925
And it's fine
if you don't wanna share them with us.

37:47.360 --> 37:50.762
But I just really think you should
share them with someone.

38:09.440 --> 38:12.364
I'd ask how you got in here...

38:13.040 --> 38:15.520
...but the Starling City vigilante
comes and goes...

38:15.720 --> 38:17.609
...as he pleases, doesn't he?

38:19.320 --> 38:21.084
How'd you know?

38:24.720 --> 38:26.404
I saw you fight.

38:29.360 --> 38:31.647
And I saw your eyes.

38:32.560 --> 38:36.201
That island changed you in ways that
only someone like me could understand.

38:36.400 --> 38:37.890
No.

38:38.240 --> 38:39.685
What you're doing right now...

38:39.920 --> 38:43.083
...I know that it feels like justice,
but it's not.

38:43.680 --> 38:49.483
-It's revenge.
- Sometimes revenge is justice.

38:52.240 --> 38:56.768
- Your father killed your fiancé.
- And what did your father do to you?

38:58.600 --> 39:03.049
Isn't the man in the hood
fighting to set things right?

39:03.240 --> 39:05.686
Why is your vendetta more valid
than mine?

39:05.880 --> 39:08.451
We're the same, you and I.

39:09.200 --> 39:11.407
- No, we're not.
- Heh.

39:11.720 --> 39:13.449
Hiding in plain sight.

39:14.280 --> 39:19.241
Concealing our anger
with smiles and lies.

39:20.400 --> 39:22.528
Don't lie to me, Oliver.

39:23.600 --> 39:25.967
You feel the same as I do. I know it.

39:26.160 --> 39:27.446
Why are you crying?

39:31.360 --> 39:33.169
I don't know.

39:34.600 --> 39:39.925
Maybe it's because I have been alone
in my hate for so long.

39:41.040 --> 39:43.691
- It feels--
- So good to tell the truth.

40:33.920 --> 40:36.002
[English - US - SDH]
